Y1  - 03-07 April 2006
PY  - 2006
KW  - Automatic control
KW  - Automation
KW  - Control systems
KW  - Costs
KW  - Data engineering
KW  - Data security
KW  - Financial management
KW  - Monitoring
KW  - Process control
KW  - Spatial databases
VL  - 
JA  - Data Engineering, 2006. ICDE '06. Proceedings of the 22nd International Conference on
DO  - 10.1109/ICDE.2006.155
AB  - The Sarbanes-Oxley Act instituted a series of corporate reforms to improve the accuracy and reliability of financial reporting. Sections 302 and 404 of the Act require SEC-reporting companies to implement internal controls over financial reporting, periodically assess the effectiveness of these internal controls, and certify the accuracy of their financial statements. We suggest that database technology can play an important role in assisting compliance with the internal control provisions of the Act. The core components of our solution include: (i) modeling of required workflows, (ii) active enforcement of control activities, (iii) auditing of actual workflows to verify compliance with internal controls, and (iv) discovery-driven OLAP to identify irregularities in financial data. We illustrate how the features of our solution fulfill Sarbanes-Oxley requirements using several real-life scenarios. In the process, we identify opportunities for new database research.
ER  - 

